definition.value: This is an AE which is one type of mast cell activation disorder (MCAD), and is an immunological condition in which mast cells inappropriately and excessively release chemical mediators, resulting in a range of chronic symptoms, sometimes including anaphylaxis or near-anaphylaxis attacks.
This is an AE which is a type of round-cell tumor consisting of mast cells.

This is an AE which refers a type of mast cell disease, is a rare disorder affecting both children and adults caused by the accumulation of functionally defective mast cells (also called mastocytes) and CD34+ mast cell precursors.
This is an AE which is a large bone marrow cell with a lobated nucleus responsible for the production of blood thrombocytes (platelets), which are necessary for normal blood clotting.
This is an AE which is the most common demyelinating disease,in which the insulating covers of nerve cells in the brain and spinal cord are damaged.
This is an AE which is a major cause of neurological disability, which accrues predominantly during progressive forms of the disease.
This is an AE which is the most common demyelinating disease and is progressive relapsing, in which the insulating covers of nerve cells in the brain and spinal cord are damaged.
This is an AE which is the most common demyelinating disease and can relapsing, in which the insulating covers of nerve cells in the brain and spinal cord are damaged.
This is an AE which begins with a clinically isolated syndrome (CIS).

This is an AE which occurs in around 65% of those with initial relapsing-remitting MS, who eventually have progressive neurologic decline between acute attacks without any definite periods of remission.
This is an AE which is considered one of the multiple sclerosis borderline diseases, which is a collection of diseases classified by some as MS variants and by others as different diseases.
This is an AE which is a bacterial infection involving the inner layers of the skin on the infusion site.
This is an AE which is blood escaping from the circulatory system from damaged blood vessels on the infusion site .
This is an AE which is a distressing feeling often caused by intense or damaging stimuli on the infusion site.
This is an AE which refers a transient abnormal enlargement of infusion site not caused by a tumor.
This is an AE which refers a somewhat high temperature on the infusion site.
This is an AE which is an iatrogenic infection occurring as an isolated case or as cluster outbreak.

This is an AE which is a type of hematoma of injection site tissue, the most common cause being capillaries damaged by trauma, causing localized bleeding that extravasates into the surrounding interstitial tissues.
This is an AE which is the accumulation of calcium salts in injection site  tissue.
This is an AE which is a closed sac on the injection site, having a distinct envelope and division compared with the nearby tissue.
This is an AE which is a harmful mutation or other deformation in injection site.
This is an AE which is inflammation of the skin on the injection site, typically characterized by itchiness, redness and a rash.
This is an AE which is the shedding of the outermost membrane or layer of a tissue, such as injection site skin.
This is an AE which is a medical condition in which there is local or more generalized decrease in normal lubrication of the skin or mucous membranes such in the injection site.
This is an AE which means "abnormal sensation" on the injection site.
This is an AE which is a chronic, relapsing, and remitting disease  on the injection site that can affect patients from infancy through adulthood.
This is an AE which removes dead injection site skin from the body and face.
This is an AE which is the leakage of a fluid out of its container into the surrounding injection site area, especially blood or blood cells from vessels.

This is an AE which is a pathological wound healing on the injection site in which connective tissue replaces normal parenchymal tissue to the extent that it goes unchecked, leading to considerable tissue remodelling and the formation of permanent scar tissue.
This is an AE which is an aggregation of macrophages that forms in response to chronic inflammation on the injection site.
This is an AE which is a condition on the injection site that involves an abnormal increase in sensitivity to stimuli of the sense.
This is an AE which is an abnormal amount of hair growth over the injection site tissue.
This is an AE which is the increase in the volume of injection site tissue due to the enlargement of its component cells.

This is an AE which is a common side effect on the injection site of various medical conditions which manifests as a reduced sense of touch or sensation, or a partial loss of sensitivity to sensory stimuli.
This is an AE which is damage to the injection site caused by an external force.
This is an AE which is a injection site state of inflammation or painful reaction to allergy or cell-lining damage.
This is an AE which refers to accumulation of fluid in an anatomic injection site joint space, usually without loculation.
This is an AE which is redness of the injection site joint skin or mucous membranes, caused by hyperemia (increased blood flow) in superficial capillaries.

This is an AE which is a procedure used in the treatment of inflammatory joint conditions, such as rheumatoid arthritis, psoriatic arthritis, gout, tendinitis, bursitis, Carpal Tunnel Syndrome, and occasionally osteoarthritis.

This is an AE which is part of the complex biological response of injection site joint tissues to harmful stimuli, such as pathogens, damaged cells, or irritants,and is a protective response involving immune cells, blood vessels, and molecular mediators.
This is an AE which is a distressing feeling on the injection site joint often caused by intense or damaging stimuli.
This is an AE which refers a transient abnormal enlargement of injection site joint area not caused by a tumor.
This is an AE which refers a somewhat high temperature on the injection site joint.

This is an AE which is a type of injury which happens relatively quickly such as in the injection site in which skin is torn, cut, or punctured (an open wound), or where blunt force trauma causes a contusion (a closed wound).
This is an AE which is a lack of muscle strength in the injection site.
This is an AE which is a form of cell injury in the injection site which results in the premature death of cells in living tissue by autolysis.
This is an AE which is injury to nervous tissue in the injection site.
This is an AE which refers a small aggregation of cells in the injection site.
This is an AE which is the build-up of fluid in the injection site tissue.
This is an AE which is a pale color of the injection site skin.
